Korea FSS Asks Banks for Dividend Moderation, MoneyToday Says

-- B y   S e o n j i n   C h a
-- 
2011-10-11T03:05:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-11/korea-fss-asks-banks-for-dividend-moderation-moneytoday-says.html
The governor of  South Korea ’s
Financial Supervisory Service asked heads of the nation’s banks
to increase lenders’ abilities to absorb potential losses, and
to refrain from paying out too much in dividends, MoneyToday
reported, citing unidentified financial industry officials.
Governor Kwon Hyouk Se made the comments at a meeting with the
bank heads this morning, the report said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Seonjin Cha in Seoul at 
 scha2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shinhye Kang at 
 skang24@bloomberg.net  